Step 1: Identify the operating cash flow from the cash flow statement.
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –18,924,462.44

Step 2: Identify the current liabilities from the balance sheet.
• Total Current Liabilities = 1,015,922.54

Step 3: Compute the Operating Cash Flow Ratio using the formula:
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)
  = –18,924,462.44 / 1,015,922.54
  ≈ –18.63

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow Ratio is –18.63.
